<p dir=3D"auto"><em>Note: many themes require installing a <a href=3D"https=
://github.com/powerline/fonts">Powerline Font</a> or a <a href=3D"https://g=
ithub.com/ryanoasis/nerd-fonts">Nerd Font</a> in order to render properly. =
Without them, these themes will render <a href=3D"https://github.com/ohmyzs=
h/ohmyzsh/wiki/FAQ#i-have-a-weird-character-in-my-prompt">weird prompt symb=
ols</a></em></p>
<p dir=3D"auto">Open up a new terminal window and your prompt should look s=
omething like this:</p>
<p dir=3D"auto"><a target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener noreferrer nofollow" h=
ref=3D"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2618447/6316862/70f58fb6-=
ba03-11e4-82c9-c083bf9a6574.png"><img src=3D"https://cloud.githubuserconten=
t.com/assets/2618447/6316862/70f58fb6-ba03-11e4-82c9-c083bf9a6574.png" alt=
=3D"Agnoster theme" style=3D"max-width: 100%;"></a></p>
<p dir=3D"auto">In case you did not find a suitable theme for your needs, p=
lease have a look at the wiki for <a href=3D"https://github.com/ohmyzsh/ohm=
yzsh/wiki/External-themes">more of them</a>.</p>
<p dir=3D"auto">If you're feeling feisty, you can let the computer select o=
ne randomly for you each time you open a new terminal window.</p>
<div class=3D"highlight highlight-source-shell notranslate position-relativ=
e overflow-auto" dir=3D"auto"><pre>ZSH_THEME=3D<span class=3D"pl-s"><span c=
lass=3D"pl-pds">"</span>random<span class=3D"pl-pds">"</span></span> <span =
class=3D"pl-c"><span class=3D"pl-c">#</span> (...please let it be pie... pl=
ease be some pie..)</span></pre><div class=3D"zeroclipboard-container">
